See as $x \to a$, the slope of the line between $(a, f(a))$ and
$(x, f(x))$ approaches the slope of the tangent line at $x = a$.

A drawing illustrating the first definition given would look something
like this:

\begin{figure}[htbp]
\centering
\includegraphics[width=.5\textwidth]{Math_Exam_Resources_Math_110_December_2010_Question_4_a_Solution_b.jpg}
